<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb9beb12c-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8" identifier="/us/usc/t18/s3733"><num value="3733">§ 3733.</num><heading> Assignment of errors—(Rule)</heading><note id="idb9beb12d-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8">
<heading style="-uslm-lc:I71" class="centered"><inline class="small-caps">See Federal Rules of Criminal Procedure</inline></heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0 fontsize7">Assignments of error on appeal abolished, Rule 37(a)(1).</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0 fontsize7">Necessity of specific objection in order to assign error in instructions, Rule 30.</p>
</note>
<sourceCredit id="idb9beb12e-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8">(<ref href="/us/act/1948-06-25/ch645">June 25, 1948, ch. 645</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/62/845">62 Stat. 845</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idb9beb12f-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idb9beb130-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I75" topic="referencesInText" id="idb9beb131-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">References in Text</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Rule 37 of the Federal Rules of Criminal Procedure was abrogated <date date="1947-12-04">Dec. 4, 1947</date>, eff. <date date="1968-07-01">July 1, 1968</date>, and is covered by Rule 3, Federal Rules of Appellate Procedure, set out in the Appendix to Title 28, Judiciary and Judicial Procedure.</p>
</note>
